<TITLE> Govt launches probe into Rangs collapse </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 9 (bdnews24.com)  The government has launched an investigation into the collapse of a floor of the beleaguered Rangs Building in Dhaka, an adviser said Sunday. A three-member committee has been asked to report in 48 hours, housing and public works adviser Mainul Hosein told reporters. "The government is not to be blamed for the incident. Actions will be taken if anyone else is found guilty in the investigation." "There will be compensation for the dead and the injured will be provided with treatment," he declared. A joint secretary to the public works ministry said the chief engineer of city development authority, Rajdhani Unnayan Kortripokkha (RAJUK), Md Shah Alam, would head the committee. The other members are a professor of the architecture department of Bangladesh University of Engineering and Technology (BUET) and an official at the public works ministry. The committee members visited the Rangs Building and would talk to the private construction firm Six Star, he said. bdnew
